dmissions and Programs  Assistive Technology Certificate  What to Expect      What to Expect  Our Assistive Technology Certificate Program (ATCP) is a flexible packaging of 12 credit hours of courses offered by the Department of Disability and Human Development (DHD).   All students are required to take DHD440 Introduction to Assistive Technology (3 credits). Students also work with the ATCP Fieldwork Coordinator to complete an AT Field Experience, a requirement for accredited AT academic programs.  Students can then choose the AT electives which they believe would best help them meet their professional goals. Students work with their ATCP Advisor to make course selections.  *Course list subject to change        Required Courses     DHD 440 Introduction to Assistive Technology: Principles and Practice 3 credit hours, Online    DHD 590 or DHD 441 ATCP Field Experience requirement      Online Electives     DHD 553 Assistive Technology for Individuals Who Are Blind or Visually Impaired 1 credit hour    DHD 554 Augmentative Communication Assessment 3 credit hours    DHD 555 AT Consideration, Assessment and Documentation in PreK-12 Educational Setting 3 credit hours    DHD 556 Seating and Positioning for Wheelchair Mobility 1 credit hour    DHD 557 Manual Wheelchair Technology 1 credit hour    DHD 558 Powered Wheelchair Technology 1 credit hour    DHD 559 Ergonomics & Safety for Workers with Disabilities 1 credit hour    DHD 567 AAC for Individuals with Autism Spectrum Disorders 2 credit hours    DHD 562 Mobile Technology and Computers: Built-in Accessibility Features 1 credit hour    DHD 568 Supporting AAC in Educational Settings 3 credit hours    DHD 569 Environmental Modification 1 credit hour    DHD 590 Field Experience in Disability & Human Development 1 credit hour    DHD 594 Assistive Technology for Early Childhood 2 credit hours    DHD 594 Assistive Technology Tools in Education 3 credit hours    DHD 594 Intro to Microcontrollers in Assistive Technology 1 credit hour    DHD 594 Technology to Support Universal Design for Learning 1 credit hour    DHD 594B 3D Printing in Assistive Technology 1-4 credit hours    DHD 594C Assistive Technology and Transportation 1-4 credit hours      Lab-Based Courses Taught at UIC     DHD 441 Adaptive Equipment Design and Fabrication 3 credit hours    DHD 551 Computers, Communication and Controls in Rehabilitation Technology 3 credit hours         Register for courses through UIC Extended Campus       Resources        Course planning chart   A program planning aid and frequently asked questions.         AHS student resources   Helpful resources across campus that offer support for you as a student.         Chancellor's Committee on the Status of Persons with Disabilities (CCSPD)   Promoting empowerment and inclusion of the faculty, staff and students with disabilities at UIC.         UIC Disability Resource Center   Empowering the UIC community with the knowledge, resources, and skills necessary to ensure full access and engagement for students with disabilities in all aspects of college life.         Disability Cultural Center   Facilitating access for students with disabilities                Disability and Human Development    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          Minor in Disability and Human Development    BS in Disability and Human Development    Expand BS in Disability and Human Development menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      MS in Disability and Human Development    PhD in Disability Studies    Expand PhD in Disability Studies menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty    Meet Our Students      Assistive Technology Certificate    Expand Assistive Technology Certificate menu          What to Expect    Applying    Faculty    Assistive Technology Certificate 